    {
      "lineNumber": 11,
      "text": "You will recall that Mr. [REDACTED] advised the Bureau of a letter which Walter Winchell had received from an individual in Los Angeles indicating that he had seen a flying saucer leave the ground within his view and which letter he theorized that this might have been a landing from another planet.",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 12,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 13,
      "text": "The Los Angeles Office was requested to locate and interview the writer of this letter, [REDACTED] Street, Los Angeles 7, California.",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 14,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 15,
      "text": "The Los Angeles Office has now advised that the [REDACTED] have no knowledge of any [REDACTED] and that other investigation to locate [REDACTED] was unproductive. It would appear, therefore, that this may have been a prank.",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 16,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 17,
      "text": "You may desire to advise Mr. [REDACTED] that there is no such person at the address given inasmuch as he indicated that Mr. Winchell intended to do a column on this letter.",
